Leaders of legislative arms across the 25 councils in Delta State have adopted Governor Ifeanyi Okowa for a second term. They endorsed Okowa at a meeting, hosted by Goru Karo, leader of the legislative arm at Udu Local Government. Addressing reporters, Chairman of Delta State Councillors Forum Victor Ofobrukueta said their endorsement followed Okowaâ€™s infrastructural transformation and smart agenda. He said 465 councillors resolved to campaign for Okowa, adding that they will buy his nomination form. Biakpara said Okowa fulfilled his promise of conducting a free and fair council election. They passed a vote of confidence in the governor and his deputy, Kingsley Otuaro.